      "topic": "Asset Misappropriation — Inventory & Assets",
      "question": "A CFE is investigating a suspected inventory theft scheme at a manufacturing company. The warehouse manager has exclusive access to inventory records and is responsible for conducting monthly physical counts. Which of the following red flags would MOST strongly indicate a potential asset misappropriation scheme involving inventory?\n\nA) Increasing gross profit margins over three consecutive quarters while inventory turnover remains constant\n\nB) Perpetual inventory records consistently showing higher quantities than physical counts, with the warehouse manager making frequent downward adjustments citing \"shrinkage\"\n\nC) Multiple purchase orders from the same vendor with slightly different pricing for identical items\n\nD) Discrepancies between the number of items shown as damaged in warehouse reports and the actual number of items disposed of through proper channels",
